</head>
<body>
<p></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:13pt"><b>Incoming Orders - Add</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></p>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">You can use this screen to add the orders that come from the Customers for products and 
services.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Customer :</b> Choose the Customer who has placed the order, from the drop down list. Typing the 
first few characters of the customer name automatically displays the relevant customer names. 
Choose the appropriate customer name by clicking on the customer name from the list.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Requested Delivery Date: </b>Enter the Date by when the delivery of Products and services are 
requested by the Customer.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Accepted Order : </b>Select this check box if you have accepted this Customer Order. This field is 
not mandatory. You can first record the Incoming Customer Order first and later analyze and 
decide to accept the Order.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Products : </b>To Choose the unique Products and Services mentioned in the Order, click on <b>+Add 
Button</b> at the right hand corner.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Name</b>: Choose the name of Product or Service from the Drop down list.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Quantity: </b>Choose the Quantity Ordered by Customer and the Unit of Measure from the Drop 
down list(Ex : Piece,Dozen etc)</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Unit Price: </b>Per unit price of the Product or Service chosen</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Sub total: </b>The Sub total (Quantity X Unit Price) is automatically calculated by the application and 
displayed in the Sub total field. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Automatically the control is moved to the next line to enable you to add more Product or Service in 
the Customer Incoming Order.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Delete :&#160;</b> At any time you wish to remove a line item(i.e Product or Service entered in the screen), 
you can remove them by clicking on the<b> Delete</b> button that appears immediately below the 
Product name.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"> </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Message : </b>Once you have completed recording all the Products and Services in the Customer 
Order, you can move to the Message field and enter any specific message or instructions from the 
Customer for this order, in the Message field.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Order :</b> Click on the Order Button to Save and close the Customer Order Screen.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Cancel : </b>Click the Cancel Button if you do not want to Save the Customer Order and wish to 
ignore the data entered.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><font color="#010101"></font></div>
</body>
